1909 def real_valued_column(column_name,
1910                        dimension=1,
1911                        default_value=None,
1912                        dtype=dtypes.float32,
1913                        normalizer=None):
1914   """Creates a `_RealValuedColumn` for dense numeric data.
1915 
1916   Args:
1917     column_name: A string defining real valued column name.
1918     dimension: An integer specifying dimension of the real valued column.
1919       The default is 1.
1920     default_value: A single value compatible with dtype or a list of values
1921       compatible with dtype which the column takes on during tf.Example parsing
1922       if data is missing. When dimension is not None, a default value of None
1923       will cause tf.parse_example to fail if an example does not contain this
1924       column. If a single value is provided, the same value will be applied as
1925       the default value for every dimension. If a list of values is provided,
1926       the length of the list should be equal to the value of `dimension`.
1927       Only scalar default value is supported in case dimension is not specified.
1928     dtype: defines the type of values. Default value is tf.float32. Must be a
1929       non-quantized, real integer or floating point type.
1930     normalizer: If not None, a function that can be used to normalize the value
1931       of the real valued column after default_value is applied for parsing.
1932       Normalizer function takes the input tensor as its argument, and returns
1933       the output tensor. (e.g. lambda x: (x - 3.0) / 4.2). Note that for
1934       variable length columns, the normalizer should expect an input_tensor of
1935       type `SparseTensor`.
1936   Returns:
1937     A _RealValuedColumn.
1938   Raises:
1939     TypeError: if dimension is not an int
1940     ValueError: if dimension is not a positive integer
1941     TypeError: if default_value is a list but its length is not equal to the
1942       value of `dimension`.
1943     TypeError: if default_value is not compatible with dtype.
1944     ValueError: if dtype is not convertible to tf.float32.
1945   """
1946 
1947   if dimension is None:
1948     raise TypeError("dimension must be an integer. Use the "
1949                     "_real_valued_var_len_column for variable length features."
1950                     "dimension: {}, column_name: {}".format(dimension,
1951                                                             column_name))
1952   if not isinstance(dimension, int):
1953     raise TypeError("dimension must be an integer. "
1954                     "dimension: {}, column_name: {}".format(dimension,
1955                                                             column_name))
1956   if dimension < 1:
1957     raise ValueError("dimension must be greater than 0. "
1958                      "dimension: {}, column_name: {}".format(dimension,
1959                                                              column_name))
1960 
1961   if not (dtype.is_integer or dtype.is_floating):
1962     raise ValueError("dtype must be convertible to float. "
1963                      "dtype: {}, column_name: {}".format(dtype, column_name))
1964 
1965   if default_value is None:
1966     return _RealValuedColumn(column_name, dimension, default_value, dtype,
1967                              normalizer)
1968 
1969   if isinstance(default_value, int):
1970     if dtype.is_integer:
1971       default_value = ([default_value for _ in range(dimension)] if dimension
1972                        else [default_value])
1973       return _RealValuedColumn(column_name, dimension, default_value, dtype,
1974                                normalizer)
1975     if dtype.is_floating:
1976       default_value = float(default_value)
1977       default_value = ([default_value for _ in range(dimension)] if dimension
1978                        else [default_value])
1979       return _RealValuedColumn(column_name, dimension, default_value, dtype,
1980                                normalizer)
1981 
1982   if isinstance(default_value, float):
1983     if dtype.is_floating and (not dtype.is_integer):
1984       default_value = ([default_value for _ in range(dimension)] if dimension
1985                        else [default_value])
1986       return _RealValuedColumn(column_name, dimension, default_value, dtype,
1987                                normalizer)
1988 
1989   if isinstance(default_value, list):
1990     if len(default_value) != dimension:
1991       raise ValueError(
1992           "The length of default_value must be equal to dimension. "
1993           "default_value: {}, dimension: {}, column_name: {}".format(
1994               default_value, dimension, column_name))
1995     # Check if the values in the list are all integers or are convertible to
1996     # floats.
1997     is_list_all_int = True
1998     is_list_all_float = True
1999     for v in default_value:
2000       if not isinstance(v, int):
2001         is_list_all_int = False
2002       if not (isinstance(v, float) or isinstance(v, int)):
2003         is_list_all_float = False
2004     if is_list_all_int:
2005       if dtype.is_integer:
2006         return _RealValuedColumn(column_name, dimension, default_value, dtype,
2007                                  normalizer)
2008       elif dtype.is_floating:
2009         default_value = [float(v) for v in default_value]
2010         return _RealValuedColumn(column_name, dimension, default_value, dtype,
2011                                  normalizer)
2012     if is_list_all_float:
2013       if dtype.is_floating and (not dtype.is_integer):
2014         default_value = [float(v) for v in default_value]
2015         return _RealValuedColumn(column_name, dimension, default_value, dtype,
2016                                  normalizer)
2017 
2018   raise TypeError("default_value must be compatible with dtype. "
2019                   "default_value: {}, dtype: {}, column_name: {}".format(
2020                       default_value, dtype, column_name))
2021 
2022 
2023 class _BucketizedColumn(
2024     _FeatureColumn,
2025     fc_core._CategoricalColumn,  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2026     fc_core._DenseColumn,  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2027     collections.namedtuple("_BucketizedColumn", ["source_column",
2028                                                  "boundaries"])):
2029   """Represents a bucketization transformation also known as binning.
2030 
2031   Instances of this class are immutable. Values in `source_column` will be
2032   bucketized based on `boundaries`.
2033   For example, if the inputs are:
2034       boundaries = [0, 10, 100]
2035       source_column = [[-5], [150], [10], [0], [4], [19]]
2036 
2037   then the bucketized feature will be:
2038       output = [[0], [3], [2], [1], [1], [2]]
2039 
2040   Attributes:
2041     source_column: A _RealValuedColumn defining dense column.
2042     boundaries: A list or tuple of floats specifying the boundaries. It has to
2043       be sorted. [a, b, c] defines following buckets: (-inf., a), [a, b),
2044       [b, c), [c, inf.)
2045   Raises:
2046     ValueError: if 'boundaries' is empty or not sorted.
2047   """
2048 
2049   def __new__(cls, source_column, boundaries):
2050     if not isinstance(source_column, _RealValuedColumn):
2051       raise TypeError("source_column must be an instance of _RealValuedColumn. "
2052                       "source_column: {}".format(source_column))
2053 
2054     if source_column.dimension is None:
2055       raise ValueError("source_column must have a defined dimension. "
2056                        "source_column: {}".format(source_column))
2057 
2058     if (not isinstance(boundaries, list) and
2059         not isinstance(boundaries, tuple)) or not boundaries:
2060       raise ValueError("boundaries must be a non-empty list or tuple. "
2061                        "boundaries: {}".format(boundaries))
2062 
2063     # We allow bucket boundaries to be monotonically increasing
2064     # (ie a[i+1] >= a[i]). When two bucket boundaries are the same, we
2065     # de-duplicate.
2066     sanitized_boundaries = []
2067     for i in range(len(boundaries) - 1):
2068       if boundaries[i] == boundaries[i + 1]:
2069         continue
2070       elif boundaries[i] < boundaries[i + 1]:
2071         sanitized_boundaries.append(boundaries[i])
2072       else:
2073         raise ValueError("boundaries must be a sorted list. "
2074                          "boundaries: {}".format(boundaries))
2075     sanitized_boundaries.append(boundaries[len(boundaries) - 1])
2076 
2077     return super(_BucketizedColumn, cls).__new__(cls, source_column,
2078                                                  tuple(sanitized_boundaries))
2079 
2080   @property
2081   def name(self):
2082     return "{}_bucketized".format(self.source_column.name)
2083 
2084   @property
2085   def length(self):
2086     """Returns total number of buckets."""
2087     return len(self.boundaries) + 1
2088 
2089   @property
2090   def config(self):
2091     return self.source_column.config
2092 
2093   @property
2094   def key(self):
2095     """Returns a string which will be used as a key when we do sorting."""
2096     return "{}".format(self)
2097 
2098   # pylint: disable=unused-argument
2099   def _to_dnn_input_layer(self,
2100                           input_tensor,
2101                           weight_collections=None,
2102                           trainable=True,
2103                           output_rank=2):
2104     if output_rank != 2:
2105       raise ValueError("BucketizedColumn currently only supports output_rank=2")
2106     return array_ops.reshape(
2107         array_ops.one_hot(
2108             math_ops.to_int64(input_tensor),
2109             self.length,
2110             1.,
2111             0.,
2112             name="one_hot"), [-1, self.length * self.source_column.dimension],
2113         name="reshape")
2114 
2115   def to_sparse_tensor(self, input_tensor):
2116     """Creates a SparseTensor from the bucketized Tensor."""
2117     dimension = self.source_column.dimension
2118     batch_size = array_ops.shape(input_tensor, name="shape")[0]
2119 
2120     if dimension > 1:
2121       i1 = array_ops.reshape(
2122           array_ops.tile(
2123               array_ops.expand_dims(
2124                   math_ops.range(0, batch_size), 1, name="expand_dims"),
2125               [1, dimension],
2126               name="tile"), [-1],
2127           name="reshape")
2128       i2 = array_ops.tile(
2129           math_ops.range(0, dimension), [batch_size], name="tile")
2130       # Flatten the bucket indices and unique them across dimensions
2131       # E.g. 2nd dimension indices will range from k to 2*k-1 with k buckets
2132       bucket_indices = array_ops.reshape(
2133           input_tensor, [-1], name="reshape") + self.length * i2
2134     else:
2135       # Simpler indices when dimension=1
2136       i1 = math_ops.range(0, batch_size)
2137       i2 = array_ops.zeros([batch_size], dtype=dtypes.int32, name="zeros")
2138       bucket_indices = array_ops.reshape(input_tensor, [-1], name="reshape")
2139 
2140     indices = math_ops.to_int64(array_ops.transpose(array_ops.stack((i1, i2))))
2141     shape = math_ops.to_int64(array_ops.stack([batch_size, dimension]))
2142     sparse_id_values = sparse_tensor_py.SparseTensor(
2143         indices, bucket_indices, shape)
2144 
2145     return sparse_id_values
2146 
2147   def _wide_embedding_lookup_arguments(self, input_tensor):
2148     return _LinearEmbeddingLookupArguments(
2149         input_tensor=self.to_sparse_tensor(input_tensor),
2150         weight_tensor=None,
2151         vocab_size=self.length * self.source_column.dimension,
2152         initializer=init_ops.zeros_initializer(),
2153         combiner="sum")
2154 
2155   def _transform_feature(self, inputs):
2156     """Handles cross transformation."""
2157     # Bucketize the source column.
2158     return bucketization_op.bucketize(
2159         inputs.get(self.source_column),
2160         boundaries=list(self.boundaries),
2161         name="bucketize")
2162 
2163   def insert_transformed_feature(self, columns_to_tensors):
2164     """Handles sparse column to id conversion."""
2165     columns_to_tensors[self] = self._transform_feature(
2166         _LazyBuilderByColumnsToTensor(columns_to_tensors))
2167 
2168   @property
2169   def _parse_example_spec(self):
2170     return self.config
2171 
2172   @property
2173   def _num_buckets(self):
2174     return self.length * self.source_column.dimension
2175 
2176   def _get_sparse_tensors(self, inputs, weight_collections=None,
2177                           trainable=None):
2178     del weight_collections
2179     del trainable
2180     return fc_core._CategoricalColumn.IdWeightPair(  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2181         self.to_sparse_tensor(inputs.get(self)), None)
2182 
2183   @property
2184   def _variable_shape(self):
2185     return tensor_shape.TensorShape(
2186         [self.length * self.source_column.dimension])
2187 
2188   def _get_dense_tensor(self, inputs, weight_collections=None, trainable=None):
2189     return self._to_dnn_input_layer(
2190         inputs.get(self), weight_collections, trainable)
2191

2193 def bucketized_column(source_column, boundaries):
2194   """Creates a _BucketizedColumn for discretizing dense input.
2195 
2196   Args:
2197     source_column: A _RealValuedColumn defining dense column.
2198     boundaries: A list or tuple of floats specifying the boundaries. It has to
2199       be sorted.
2200 
2201   Returns:
2202     A _BucketizedColumn.
2203 
2204   Raises:
2205     ValueError: if 'boundaries' is empty or not sorted.
2206   """
2207   return _BucketizedColumn(source_column, boundaries)

2209 
2210 class _CrossedColumn(
2211     _FeatureColumn,
2212     fc_core._CategoricalColumn,  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2213     collections.namedtuple("_CrossedColumn", [
2214         "columns", "hash_bucket_size", "hash_key", "combiner",
2215         "ckpt_to_load_from", "tensor_name_in_ckpt"
2216     ])):
2217   """Represents a cross transformation also known as conjunction or combination.
2218 
2219   Instances of this class are immutable. It crosses given `columns`. Crossed
2220   column output will be hashed to hash_bucket_size.
2221   Conceptually, transformation can be thought as:
2222     Hash(cartesian product of features in columns) % `hash_bucket_size`
2223 
2224   For example, if the columns are
2225 
2226       SparseTensor referred by first column: shape = [2, 2]
2227       [0, 0]: "a"
2228       [1, 0]: "b"
2229       [1, 1]: "c"
2230 
2231       SparseTensor referred by second column: : shape = [2, 1]
2232       [0, 0]: "d"
2233       [1, 0]: "e"
2234 
2235   then crossed feature will look like:
2236 
2237       shape = [2, 2]
2238       [0, 0]: Hash64("d", Hash64("a")) % hash_bucket_size
2239       [1, 0]: Hash64("e", Hash64("b")) % hash_bucket_size
2240       [1, 1]: Hash64("e", Hash64("c")) % hash_bucket_size
2241 
2242   Attributes:
2243     columns: An iterable of _FeatureColumn. Items can be an instance of
2244       _SparseColumn, _CrossedColumn, or _BucketizedColumn.
2245     hash_bucket_size: An int that is > 1. The number of buckets.
2246     combiner: A string specifying how to reduce if there are multiple entries
2247       in a single row. Currently "mean", "sqrtn" and "sum" are supported, with
2248       "sum" the default. "sqrtn" often achieves good accuracy, in particular
2249       with bag-of-words columns. Each of this can be thought as example level
2250       normalizations on the column::
2251         * "sum": do not normalize
2252         * "mean": do l1 normalization
2253         * "sqrtn": do l2 normalization
2254       For more information: `tf.embedding_lookup_sparse`.
2255     ckpt_to_load_from: (Optional). String representing checkpoint name/pattern
2256       to restore the column weights. Required if `tensor_name_in_ckpt` is not
2257       None.
2258     tensor_name_in_ckpt: (Optional). Name of the `Tensor` in the provided
2259       checkpoint from which to restore the column weights. Required if
2260       `ckpt_to_load_from` is not None.
2261 
2262   Raises:
2263     TypeError: if all items in columns are not an instance of _SparseColumn,
2264       _CrossedColumn, or _BucketizedColumn.
2265     ValueError: if hash_bucket_size is not > 1 or len(columns) is not > 1. Also,
2266       if only one of `ckpt_to_load_from` and `tensor_name_in_ckpt` is specified.
2267   """
2268 
2269   @staticmethod
2270   def _assert_is_crossable(column):
2271     if isinstance(column, (_SparseColumn, _CrossedColumn, _BucketizedColumn)):
2272       return
2273     raise TypeError("columns must be a set of _SparseColumn, "
2274                     "_CrossedColumn, or _BucketizedColumn instances. "
2275                     "(column {} is a {})".format(column,
2276                                                  column.__class__.__name__))
2277 
2278   def __new__(cls,
2279               columns,
2280               hash_bucket_size,
2281               hash_key,
2282               combiner="sum",
2283               ckpt_to_load_from=None,
2284               tensor_name_in_ckpt=None):
2285     for column in columns:
2286       _CrossedColumn._assert_is_crossable(column)
2287 
2288     if len(columns) < 2:
2289       raise ValueError("columns must contain at least 2 elements. "
2290                        "columns: {}".format(columns))
2291 
2292     if hash_bucket_size < 2:
2293       raise ValueError("hash_bucket_size must be at least 2. "
2294                        "hash_bucket_size: {}".format(hash_bucket_size))
2295 
2296     if (ckpt_to_load_from is None) != (tensor_name_in_ckpt is None):
2297       raise ValueError("Must specify both `ckpt_to_load_from` and "
2298                        "`tensor_name_in_ckpt` or none of them.")
2299 
2300     sorted_columns = sorted(
2301         [column for column in columns], key=lambda column: column.name)
2302     return super(_CrossedColumn, cls).__new__(cls, tuple(sorted_columns),
2303                                               hash_bucket_size, hash_key,
2304                                               combiner,
2305                                               ckpt_to_load_from,
2306                                               tensor_name_in_ckpt)
2307 
2308   @property
2309   def name(self):
2310     sorted_names = sorted([column.name for column in self.columns])
2311     return "_X_".join(sorted_names)
2312 
2313   @property
2314   def config(self):
2315     config = {}
2316     for column in self.columns:
2317       config.update(_get_feature_config(column))
2318     return config
2319 
2320   @property
2321   def length(self):
2322     """Returns total number of buckets."""
2323     return self.hash_bucket_size
2324 
2325   @property
2326   def key(self):
2327     """Returns a string which will be used as a key when we do sorting."""
2328     return "{}".format(self)
2329 
2330   def id_tensor(self, input_tensor):
2331     """Returns the id tensor from the given transformed input_tensor."""
2332     return input_tensor
2333 
2334   def weight_tensor(self, input_tensor):
2335     """Returns the weight tensor from the given transformed input_tensor."""
2336     del input_tensor
2337     return None
2338 
2339   def _to_dnn_input_layer(self,
2340                           input_tensor,
2341                           weight_collections=None,
2342                           trainable=True,
2343                           output_rank=2):
2344     del input_tensor
2345     del weight_collections
2346     del trainable
2347     del output_rank
2348     raise ValueError("CrossedColumn is not supported in DNN. "
2349                      "Please use embedding_column. column: {}".format(self))
2350 
2351   def _checkpoint_path(self):
2352     if self.ckpt_to_load_from is not None:
2353       return self.ckpt_to_load_from, self.tensor_name_in_ckpt
2354     return None
2355 
2356   def _wide_embedding_lookup_arguments(self, input_tensor):
2357     return _LinearEmbeddingLookupArguments(
2358         input_tensor=input_tensor,
2359         weight_tensor=None,
2360         vocab_size=self.length,
2361         initializer=init_ops.zeros_initializer(),
2362         combiner=self.combiner)
2363 
2364   def _transform_feature(self, inputs):
2365     """Handles cross transformation."""
2366 
2367     def _collect_leaf_level_columns(cross):
2368       """Collects base columns contained in the cross."""
2369       leaf_level_columns = []
2370       for c in cross.columns:
2371         if isinstance(c, _CrossedColumn):
2372           leaf_level_columns.extend(_collect_leaf_level_columns(c))
2373         else:
2374           leaf_level_columns.append(c)
2375       return leaf_level_columns
2376 
2377     feature_tensors = []
2378     for c in _collect_leaf_level_columns(self):
2379       if isinstance(c, _SparseColumn):
2380         feature_tensors.append(inputs.get(c.name))
2381       else:
2382         if isinstance(c, _BucketizedColumn):
2383           feature_tensors.append(c.to_sparse_tensor(inputs.get(c)))
2384         else:
2385           feature_tensors.append(inputs.get(c))
2386     return sparse_feature_cross_op.sparse_feature_cross(
2387         feature_tensors,
2388         hashed_output=True,
2389         num_buckets=self.hash_bucket_size,
2390         hash_key=self.hash_key,
2391         name="cross")
2392 
2393   def insert_transformed_feature(self, columns_to_tensors):
2394     """Handles sparse column to id conversion."""
2395     columns_to_tensors[self] = self._transform_feature(
2396         _LazyBuilderByColumnsToTensor(columns_to_tensors))
2397 
2398   @property
2399   def _parse_example_spec(self):
2400     return self.config
2401 
2402   @property
2403   def _num_buckets(self):
2404     return self.length
2405 
2406   def _get_sparse_tensors(self, inputs, weight_collections=None,
2407                           trainable=None):
2408     del weight_collections
2409     del trainable
2410     return fc_core._CategoricalColumn.IdWeightPair(inputs.get(self), None)  # pylint: disable=protected-access

2413 class _LazyBuilderByColumnsToTensor(object):
2414 
2415   def __init__(self, columns_to_tensors):
2416     self._columns_to_tensors = columns_to_tensors
2417 
2418   def get(self, key):
2419     """Gets the transformed feature column."""
2420     if key in self._columns_to_tensors:
2421       return self._columns_to_tensors[key]
2422     if isinstance(key, str):
2423       raise ValueError(
2424           "features dictionary doesn't contain key ({})".format(key))
2425     if not isinstance(key, _FeatureColumn):
2426       raise TypeError('"key" must be either a "str" or "_FeatureColumn". '
2427                       "Provided: {}".format(key))
2428 
2429     key.insert_transformed_feature(self._columns_to_tensors)
2430     return self._columns_to_tensors[key]

2433 def crossed_column(columns, hash_bucket_size, combiner="sum",
2434                    ckpt_to_load_from=None,
2435                    tensor_name_in_ckpt=None,
2436                    hash_key=None):
2437   """Creates a _CrossedColumn for performing feature crosses.
2438 
2439   Args:
2440     columns: An iterable of _FeatureColumn. Items can be an instance of
2441       _SparseColumn, _CrossedColumn, or _BucketizedColumn.
2442     hash_bucket_size: An int that is > 1. The number of buckets.
2443     combiner: A string specifying how to reduce if there are multiple entries
2444       in a single row. Currently "mean", "sqrtn" and "sum" are supported, with
2445       "sum" the default. "sqrtn" often achieves good accuracy, in particular
2446       with bag-of-words columns. Each of this can be thought as example level
2447       normalizations on the column::
2448         * "sum": do not normalize
2449         * "mean": do l1 normalization
2450         * "sqrtn": do l2 normalization
2451       For more information: `tf.embedding_lookup_sparse`.
2452     ckpt_to_load_from: (Optional). String representing checkpoint name/pattern
2453       to restore the column weights. Required if `tensor_name_in_ckpt` is not
2454       None.
2455     tensor_name_in_ckpt: (Optional). Name of the `Tensor` in the provided
2456       checkpoint from which to restore the column weights. Required if
2457       `ckpt_to_load_from` is not None.
2458     hash_key: Specify the hash_key that will be used by the `FingerprintCat64`
2459       function to combine the crosses fingerprints on SparseFeatureCrossOp
2460       (optional).
2461 
2462   Returns:
2463     A _CrossedColumn.
2464 
2465   Raises:
2466     TypeError: if any item in columns is not an instance of _SparseColumn,
2467       _CrossedColumn, or _BucketizedColumn, or
2468       hash_bucket_size is not an int.
2469     ValueError: if hash_bucket_size is not > 1 or
2470       len(columns) is not > 1.
2471   """
2472   return _CrossedColumn(
2473       columns,
2474       hash_bucket_size,
2475       hash_key,
2476       combiner=combiner,
2477       ckpt_to_load_from=ckpt_to_load_from,
2478       tensor_name_in_ckpt=tensor_name_in_ckpt)
2479

2481 class DataFrameColumn(_FeatureColumn,
2482                       collections.namedtuple("DataFrameColumn",
2483                                              ["column_name", "series"])):
2484   """Represents a feature column produced from a `DataFrame`.
2485 
2486   Instances of this class are immutable.  A `DataFrame` column may be dense or
2487   sparse, and may have any shape, with the constraint that dimension 0 is
2488   batch_size.
2489 
2490   Args:
2491     column_name: a name for this column
2492     series: a `Series` to be wrapped, which has already had its base features
2493       substituted with `PredefinedSeries`.
2494   """
2495 
2496   def __new__(cls, column_name, series):
2497     return super(DataFrameColumn, cls).__new__(cls, column_name, series)
2498 
2499   @property
2500   def name(self):
2501     return self.column_name
2502 
2503   @property
2504   def config(self):
2505     return self.series.required_base_features()
2506 
2507   @property
2508   def key(self):
2509     """Returns a string which will be used as a key when we do sorting."""
2510     return self.name
2511 
2512   def insert_transformed_feature(self, columns_to_tensors):
2513     # The cache must already contain mappings from the expected base feature
2514     # names to Tensors.
2515 
2516     # Passing columns_to_tensors as the cache here means that multiple outputs
2517     # of the transform will be cached, keyed by the repr of their associated
2518     # TransformedSeries.
2519     # The specific requested output ends up in columns_to_tensors twice: once
2520     # keyed by the TransformedSeries repr, and once keyed by this
2521     # DataFrameColumn instance.
2522     columns_to_tensors[self] = self.series.build(columns_to_tensors)
2523 
2524   # pylint: disable=unused-argument
2525   def _to_dnn_input_layer(self,
2526                           input_tensor,
2527                           weight_collections=None,
2528                           trainable=True,
2529                           output_rank=2):
2530     if input_tensor.dtype != dtypes.float32:
2531       input_tensor = math_ops.to_float(input_tensor)
2532     return _reshape_real_valued_tensor(input_tensor, output_rank, self.name)
2533 
2534   def _to_dense_tensor(self, input_tensor):
2535     return self._to_dnn_input_layer(input_tensor)
2536 
2537   def __eq__(self, other):
2538     if isinstance(other, self.__class__):
2539       return self.__dict__ == other.__dict__
2540     else:
2541       return False
2542 
2543   def __ne__(self, other):
2544     return not self.__eq__(other)

2547 def _get_feature_config(feature_column):
2548   """Returns configuration for the base feature defined in feature_column."""
2549   if not isinstance(feature_column, _FeatureColumn):
2550     raise TypeError(
2551         "feature_columns should only contain instances of _FeatureColumn. "
2552         "Given column is {}".format(feature_column))
2553   if isinstance(feature_column, (_SparseColumn, _WeightedSparseColumn,
2554                                  _EmbeddingColumn, _RealValuedColumn,
2555                                  _RealValuedVarLenColumn,
2556                                  _BucketizedColumn, _CrossedColumn,
2557                                  _OneHotColumn, _ScatteredEmbeddingColumn)):
2558     return feature_column.config
2559 
2560   raise TypeError("Not supported _FeatureColumn type. "
2561                   "Given column is {}".format(feature_column))

2563 
2564 def create_feature_spec_for_parsing(feature_columns):
2565   """Helper that prepares features config from input feature_columns.
2566 
2567   The returned feature config can be used as arg 'features' in tf.parse_example.
2568 
2569   Typical usage example:
2570 
2571   ```python
2572   # Define features and transformations
2573   feature_a = sparse_column_with_vocabulary_file(...)
2574   feature_b = real_valued_column(...)
2575   feature_c_bucketized = bucketized_column(real_valued_column("feature_c"), ...)
2576   feature_a_x_feature_c = crossed_column(
2577     columns=[feature_a, feature_c_bucketized], ...)
2578 
2579   feature_columns = set(
2580     [feature_b, feature_c_bucketized, feature_a_x_feature_c])
2581   batch_examples = tf.parse_example(
2582       serialized=serialized_examples,
2583       features=create_feature_spec_for_parsing(feature_columns))
2584   ```
2585 
2586   For the above example, create_feature_spec_for_parsing would return the dict:
2587   {
2588     "feature_a": parsing_ops.VarLenFeature(tf.string),
2589     "feature_b": parsing_ops.FixedLenFeature([1], dtype=tf.float32),
2590     "feature_c": parsing_ops.FixedLenFeature([1], dtype=tf.float32)
2591   }
2592 
2593   Args:
2594     feature_columns: An iterable containing all the feature columns. All items
2595       should be instances of classes derived from _FeatureColumn, unless
2596       feature_columns is a dict -- in which case, this should be true of all
2597       values in the dict.
2598   Returns:
2599     A dict mapping feature keys to FixedLenFeature or VarLenFeature values.
2600   """
2601   if isinstance(feature_columns, dict):
2602     feature_columns = feature_columns.values()
2603 
2604   features_config = {}
2605   for column in feature_columns:
2606     features_config.update(_get_feature_config(column))
2607   return features_config
2608 
2609 
2610 def _create_sequence_feature_spec_for_parsing(sequence_feature_columns,
2611                                               allow_missing_by_default=False):
2612   """Prepares a feature spec for parsing `tf.SequenceExample`s.
2613 
2614   Args:
2615     sequence_feature_columns: an iterable containing all the feature columns.
2616       All items should be instances of classes derived from `_FeatureColumn`.
2617     allow_missing_by_default: whether to set `allow_missing=True` by default for
2618       `FixedLenSequenceFeature`s.
2619   Returns:
2620     A dict mapping feature keys to `FixedLenSequenceFeature` or `VarLenFeature`.
2621   """
2622   feature_spec = create_feature_spec_for_parsing(sequence_feature_columns)
2623   sequence_feature_spec = {}
2624   for key, feature in feature_spec.items():
2625     if isinstance(feature, parsing_ops.VarLenFeature):
2626       sequence_feature = feature
2627     elif (isinstance(feature, parsing_ops.FixedLenFeature) or
2628           isinstance(feature, parsing_ops.FixedLenSequenceFeature)):
2629       default_is_set = feature.default_value is not None
2630       if default_is_set:
2631         logging.warning(
2632             'Found default value {} for feature "{}". Ignoring this value and '
2633             'setting `allow_missing=True` instead.'.
2634             format(feature.default_value, key))
2635       sequence_feature = parsing_ops.FixedLenSequenceFeature(
2636           shape=feature.shape,
2637           dtype=feature.dtype,
2638           allow_missing=(allow_missing_by_default or default_is_set))
2639     else:
2640       raise TypeError(
2641           "Unsupported feature type: {}".format(type(feature).__name__))
2642     sequence_feature_spec[key] = sequence_feature
2643   return sequence_feature_spec
2644 
2645 
2646 def make_place_holder_tensors_for_base_features(feature_columns):
2647   """Returns placeholder tensors for inference.
2648 
2649   Args:
2650     feature_columns: An iterable containing all the feature columns. All items
2651       should be instances of classes derived from _FeatureColumn.
2652   Returns:
2653     A dict mapping feature keys to SparseTensors (sparse columns) or
2654     placeholder Tensors (dense columns).
2655   """
2656   # Get dict mapping features to FixedLenFeature or VarLenFeature values.
2657   dict_for_parse_example = create_feature_spec_for_parsing(feature_columns)
2658   placeholders = {}
2659   for column_name, column_type in dict_for_parse_example.items():
2660     if isinstance(column_type, parsing_ops.VarLenFeature):
2661       # Sparse placeholder for sparse tensors.
2662       placeholders[column_name] = array_ops.sparse_placeholder(
2663           column_type.dtype, name="Placeholder_{}".format(column_name))
2664     else:
2665       # Simple placeholder for dense tensors.
2666       placeholders[column_name] = array_ops.placeholder(
2667           column_type.dtype,
2668           shape=(None, column_type.shape[0]),
2669           name="Placeholder_{}".format(column_name))
2670   return placeholders

2673 class _SparseIdLookupConfig(

2687     num_oov_buckets: The number of out-of-vocabulary buckets. If zero all out of
2688       vocabulary features will be ignored.
2689     vocab_size: Number of the elements in the vocabulary.
2690     default_value: The value to use for out-of-vocabulary feature values.
2691       Defaults to -1.
2692   """
2693 
2694   def __new__(cls,
2695               vocabulary_file=None,
2696               keys=None,
2697               num_oov_buckets=0,
2698               vocab_size=None,
2699               default_value=-1):
2700 
2701     return super(_SparseIdLookupConfig, cls).__new__(cls, vocabulary_file, keys,
2702                                                      num_oov_buckets,
2703                                                      vocab_size, default_value)
